rawobject Configuration object of the flow of a highbond robots or workflow robots.It contains user python scripts and variables set up in flow builder.See example of the flow structure in the sample response.Version in json is required.Initial version of flow json is version: '2021-02-05'.environment is execution environments for user scripts.Each environment consists of a runtime (e.g.‚Äúpython3.11‚Äù) and a list of packages (e.g."hcl==3.0.*", "boxsdk==3.9.2")
environment for a robot should have runtime: "python3.11" and requirements should include hcl==3.0.*.For HighBond Robot, additional packages can be included, however they should match the versions as given below:

Workflow Robot

environment: {
  runtime: "python3.11",
  requirements: [
    "hcl==3.0.*"
  ]
}


HighBond Robot

environment: {
  runtime: "python3.11", 
  requirements: [
    "hcl==3.0.*",
    "boxsdk==3.9.2",
    "openpyxl==3.1.2",
    "Jinja2==3.1.3",
    "simple-salesforce==1.12.5",
    "jira==3.8.0"
   ]
 }In case environment is missing or the packages (e.g boxsdk and others mentioned above) does not match the specified versions, API will throw an error.id in flow json needs to be unique.Example shown are using uuidv4.Note: For the hcl requirement, specify a version that is a valid HCL library version number using this format: major.minor.* (For example, hcl==3.0.*) Use an asterisk (*) rather than a specific patch number.{
  version: '2021-02-05',
